        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 6 at 3:14PM CDT until May 6 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 314 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Karnack to 6 miles south of Deberry, moving east
at 60 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Deberry, Jonesville, Waskom, Midyett, Elysian Fields, Leigh,
Scottsville, and Marshall.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for northwestern
Louisiana...and northeastern Texas.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
